# room-booking — agent context

Before non-trivial edits, read **`AGENTS.md`** (agent memory) and **`README.md`** (setup, prod checklist, Keycloak).

## Auth

- **Server**: `lib/auth.ts` + **`lib/auth-public.ts`** (`getBetterAuthPublicBaseUrl`, `buildBetterAuthTrustedOrigins`), handler `app/api/auth/[...all]/route.ts`.
- **Client**: `lib/auth-client.ts` — set **`NEXT_PUBLIC_BETTER_AUTH_URL`** same as **`BETTER_AUTH_URL`** in production; rebuild after changing it.
- **Sign-in**: `app/sign-in/page.tsx` — OAuth with **`disableRedirect: true`**, then **`window.location.assign`**; toasts on failure.
- **Gate**: `middleware.ts` → `/sign-in` if no session cookie.
- **APIs**: `lib/require-session.ts` — **`requireApiSession()`**; **`bookingActorFromSessionUser()`** for **`bookedBy`** / **`bookedByEmail`** (never from untrusted body).

## Data

- Bookings: **`data/bookings.json`**, **`lib/db.ts`**, **`app/api/bookings/**`**
- Sessions: **`data/auth.db`** (gitignored; persist via Docker volume `./data`)

## Env reference

`.env.example` — **`BETTER_AUTH_*`**, **`NEXT_PUBLIC_BETTER_AUTH_URL`**, **`KEYCLOAK_*`**, optional **`BETTER_AUTH_TRUSTED_ORIGINS`**. Keycloak callback: **`{BETTER_AUTH_URL}/api/auth/oauth2/callback/keycloak`**.

When auth or identity rules change, update **README**, **AGENTS**, **`.env.example`**, and this rule if it affects defaults or file locations.
